antiken Rezeptionsgeschichte, an denen deutlich wird, dass sich der dynamische Prozess der Auslegung, der in der Literargeschichte des Pentateuchs zu greifen ist, nicht nur in den biblischen Handschriften, sondern auch in anderen Texten vom Toten Meer fortsetzt  aThis volume contains contributions to Pentateuch research from the past twenty years, arranged according to thematic criteria, which are further explained in the introductions to the five sections and placed within the broader context of Pentateuch analysis: the literary problem of the Pentateuch; ancient history and patriarchs; the law between exodus and Canaan; the Torah and former prophets; the reception of the Torah in the Dead Sea Scrolls.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 4aHexateuch. 4aPentateuch, Komposition. 4aQumranschriften. 4aTorarezeption.  aHexateuch.  aPentateuch.  aTora reception in Qumran.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2024 Part 1z97831113321920 cEPUBz97831113676820 cprintz978311136631940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311136705740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111367057423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111367057/original  a978-3-11-133219-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2024 Part 1b2024  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles